285 g Jumbo Shrimp
350 g Cheese Tortellini
6 unit(s) Wooden Skewers
113 g Baby Heirloom Tomatoes
½ cup Basil Pesto
1 unit(s) Corn on the Cob
¼ cup Feta Cheese, crumbled
7 g Basil
2 tbsp Zesty Garlic Blend
28 g Pine Nuts
1.5 tbsp Oil*
¼ tsp Salt*
0.13 tsp Pepper*

Add 10 cups water and 1 tbsp salt to a large pot (use same for 4 ppl). Cover and bring to a boil over high heat.
Meanwhile, husk corn.
Quater tomatoes.
Drain, rinse then pat shrimp dry with a paper towel. Add shrimp, 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) oil and Zesty Garlic Spice blend to a large bowl. Season with salt, then toss to coat. Set aside
Soak skewers in water, 5 min.

Meanwhile, heat a large non-stick pan over medium-high heat.
When hot, add pine nuts to the dry pan. Toast, stirring often, until golden, 3-4 min. (TIP: Keep your eye on them so they don't burn.) Transfer to a plate.

Add tortellini to the boiling water. Cook, stirring occasionally, until tender, 2-3 min.
Reserve 1/4 cup (1/2 cup) pasta water, then drain.
Add tortellini to a large bowl with half the pesto and reserved pasta water. Toss to coat. Set aside.

Drain skewers, then thread shrimp onto skewers. Place assembled skewers on a plate to bring to the grill.

Add corn to grill. Close lid and grill, turning occasionally, until tender and grill marks form, 8-10 min.
When corn is almost done, add shrimp skewers to other side of the grill. Close lid and grill for 1-3 min per side, until opaque.**

Once corn has cooled slighty, halve cobs crosswise. Place cut-side of cobs down on the cutting board. Moving the knife along the cob in a downward motion, shave corn kernels off.
Add corn kernels, tomatoes, feta and remaining pesto to the large bowl with the tortellini. Season with salt and pepper, then stir to combine.
Divide pesto tortellini between plates. Top with pine nuts and shrimp.
Tear basil over top.